<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="765" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d765">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–1647</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Forrestal</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-16">April 16,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Referring to your letter of
                        April 9, I have been informed by Commander Naval Forces, Western Pacific,
                        that Nationalist authorities were to be notified on April 14 of our
                        intentions to abandon the ammunition dumps at HsinHo and at airfield
                        Peiping. He estimated that the Nationalist troops could assume
                        responsibilities for guarding this ammunition by April 21.</p>
                    <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Forrestal</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>